The paper is about a system for detecting online transaction fraud, which is a common problem in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The system uses machine learning techniques for feature extraction and detection, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system's effectiveness and efficiency are evaluated through extensive experiments, which involves data analysis and statistical modeling, indicating the relevance of machine learning and data science (cs.LG, cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the implementation and deployment of the system, which involves software engineering practices (cs.SE).
